<p><b>Is automotive engineering and automobile engineering the same?</b> Automobile refers to four-wheeled vehicles used for transport while automotive relates to all motor vehicles. Hence, automobile engineers may work specifically on the design and manufacture of cars, whereas automotive engineers deal with all vehicles, including public transport.</p>
<p><b>Which is better, mechanical or automobile engineering?</b> Their differences and similarities While mechanical engineering is a more general field that covers a wide range of mechanical systems and devices, automobile engineering is a subset of mechanical engineering that is especially focused on the design, development, and production of automobiles.</p>
